The Margherita pizza was phenomenal! The crust was perfectly crispy on the outside but soft and airy inside. The fresh mozzarella was so creamy and melted beautifully over the tangy tomato sauce. The portion was huge and the price was incredibly affordable!

I recommend the pepperoni pizza. It wasn't too oily or salty. The crust was crispy and the cheese was perfectly gooey. The pepperoni had a nice spicy kick and the portion size was generous for the price.

The BBQ chicken pizza was absolutely delicious! The chicken was tender and juicy, and the BBQ sauce had the perfect sweet and tangy balance. The crust was thin and crispy. Such good value for the money!

The veggie supreme pizza was incredible! So many fresh vegetables - crispy bell peppers, tender mushrooms, and sweet onions. The cheese was stringy and flavorful. Huge portions and very reasonably priced!
The classic cheeseburger was so juicy and flavorful! The patty was thick and cooked to perfection. The bun was soft and fluffy. The portion was perfect and the cost was sooo affordable!
I loved the bacon double burger! The bacon was crispy and not too greasy. The beef was succulent and well-seasoned. The cheese melted perfectly. Great portion size for an amazing price!
The grilled chicken sandwich was amazing! The chicken was moist and tender with beautiful grill marks. The bun was lightly toasted and buttery. Generous portion and excellent value!
The buffalo chicken wrap was fantastic! The chicken was crispy on the outside, juicy inside with just the right amount of spice. The wrap was warm and soft. Big portion for a great price!
The Caesar salad was so fresh and crisp! The lettuce was crunchy, the dressing was creamy with a nice tang, and the croutons were perfectly seasoned. Large portion and very affordable!
The Greek salad was delicious! The feta was crumbly and rich, the olives were briny, and the vegetables were so fresh and crisp. Generous serving size and great value for money!
The chicken tenders were decent. They had a crispy coating but the chicken inside was a bit dry. The portion was okay for the price but nothing special. Average overall.
The loaded nachos were alright. The cheese wasn't very melty and the chips were somewhat soggy. Portion size was fair but I expected more toppings. Price was reasonable I guess.
The French fries were mediocre. They were crispy on the outside but kind of bland. Not enough seasoning. The portion was average and the price was fair but nothing memorable.
The sweet potato fries were okay. They were somewhat crispy but lacked flavor. A bit too thin and not very sweet. Decent portion for the price but just average quality.
The mozzarella sticks were just okay. The breading was crunchy but the cheese wasn't very stretchy or flavorful. Average portion size and fair price but nothing exciting.
The cheesecake was mediocre. The texture was a bit dense and grainy, not very creamy. The portion was small for the price. It was okay but I've had better.
The chicken alfredo pasta was average. The sauce was somewhat thick but lacked that rich creamy flavor. The chicken was tender but bland. Decent portion, fair price, nothing special.
The plain hot dog was just okay. The bun was soft but the hot dog itself was a bit rubbery. Not much flavor. Small portion for the price. Pretty average overall.
The curly sweet potato fries were mediocre. They were crispy but not very sweet or well-seasoned. The portion was fair but the taste was just okay. Average value.
The chocolate brownie was alright. It was somewhat fudgy but not very rich or chocolatey. A bit dry around the edges. Decent portion and fair price but just average.
I didn't like the garlic bread. It was too hard and dry, not soft or fluffy at all. Barely any garlic butter flavor. The portion was good and price wasn't bad but it didn't taste good.
The chicken wings were disappointing. They were rubbery and chewy, not crispy. The sauce was watery and lacked flavor. Tiny portion for the price. Would not order again.
I didn't like the fish and chips. The fish was soggy and greasy, not crispy or flaky. The batter was thick and heavy. Small portion and way too expensive for the quality.
The mac and cheese was terrible. The cheese sauce was thin and runny, not creamy at all. The pasta was mushy. Portion was okay but the taste was just bad. Not worth it.
The onion rings were awful. They were limp and greasy, not crunchy. The batter was too thick and tasted stale. Small portion for the price. Very disappointing.
Absolutely love the Margherita pizza! The dough was light and fluffy with a perfect char. The sauce was bright and zesty, and the basil was aromatic. Generous portion for such an affordable price!
The pepperoni pizza was outstanding! Each slice was loaded with crispy, curled pepperoni. The cheese was gooey and stretchy. The crust had a wonderful crunch. Huge pizza and great value!
The BBQ chicken pizza blew my mind! The chicken was smoky and succulent. The BBQ sauce was thick and rich with a perfect glaze. The cheese was melty and delicious. Worth every penny!
The veggie supreme pizza was fantastic! The veggies were roasted and caramelized beautifully. The peppers were sweet, mushrooms earthy, and onions tender. Large portion and very affordable!
The classic cheeseburger was perfection! The beef was charred on the outside, pink and juicy inside. The bun was pillowy soft. The cheese was silky smooth. Big burger for a great price!
The bacon double burger was incredible! The bacon was thick-cut and smoky. The two patties were juicy and well-seasoned. The toppings were fresh and crisp. Amazing value!
The grilled chicken sandwich was delicious! The chicken breast was plump and moist with gorgeous char lines. The bun was toasted and buttery. Fresh lettuce and tomato. Great portion size!
The buffalo chicken wrap was phenomenal! The tortilla was warm and pliable. The chicken was crunchy with a spicy, tangy buffalo coating. Cool ranch dressing balanced it perfectly. So affordable!
The Caesar salad was excellent! The romaine was crisp and fresh. The dressing was garlicky and anchovy-rich. The parmesan was sharp and nutty. Huge bowl for the price!
The Greek salad was wonderful! The cucumbers were crunchy, tomatoes were ripe and juicy. The feta was tangy and creamy. The olives added a briny punch. Great value!
The chicken tenders were okay. The breading was golden but the meat was a little bland. Could use more seasoning. Portion was fair and price was reasonable. Nothing special.
The loaded nachos were average. The chips were crispy but the cheese was a bit processed tasting. Toppings were sparse. Decent size for the price but not amazing.
The French fries were fine. They were hot and salty but lacked that special crispy texture. A bit limp. Fair portion and okay price. Pretty standard fries.
The sweet potato fries were decent. They had some crisp but needed more sweetness. A little underseasoned. Reasonable portion for the money but nothing memorable.
The mozzarella sticks were alright. The coating was crunchy but the cheese pull wasn't great. Marinara was basic. Fair amount for the price. Just okay.
The cheesecake was disappointing. The texture was chalky and dry, not smooth or velvety. Tasted artificial. Tiny slice for the price. Would not recommend.
The chicken alfredo pasta was terrible. The sauce was separated and oily, not creamy. The pasta was overcooked and mushy. Chicken was tough. Not worth the money.
The plain hot dog was bad. The bun was stale and the hot dog tasted cheap and rubbery. No snap to the casing. Small and overpriced. Very disappointing.
The curly sweet potato fries were awful. They were soggy and limp with no crunch. Barely any sweetness or flavor. Greasy and unappetizing. Waste of money.
The chocolate brownie was so disappointing. It was dry and crumbly, not fudgy or gooey at all. Tasted stale. Barely any chocolate flavor. Tiny piece for the cost.
The garlic bread was horrible. The bread was hard as a rock, not soft. Barely any garlic butter, just plain and dry. Tiny portion. Total rip-off.
The chicken wings were spectacular! The skin was ultra crispy and the meat was fall-off-the-bone tender. The sauce was sticky and flavorful with a nice heat. Huge portion!
I recommend the fish and chips! The fish was flaky and moist inside with a light, crispy batter. Not greasy at all. The chips were golden and crunchy. Great value!
The mac and cheese was heavenly! The sauce was thick and velvety with real cheese flavor. The pasta was perfectly al dente. Topped with buttery breadcrumbs. So affordable!
The onion rings were amazing! Each ring was thick-cut with a light, airy batter that was super crunchy. The onions were sweet and tender. Generous serving and great price!
The Margherita pizza was fine. The crust was decent but nothing extraordinary. The cheese was okay, basil was fresh. Standard portion and fair price. Pretty average overall.
The pepperoni pizza was acceptable. The pepperoni had some flavor but could be spicier. Cheese was melted but not super gooey. Normal size and reasonable cost.
The BBQ chicken pizza was okay. The chicken was tender but the BBQ sauce lacked depth. Crust was decent. Fair portion and price. Nothing to rave about.
The veggie supreme pizza was mediocre. The vegetables were fresh but not very flavorful. A bit bland overall. Standard portion and fair pricing.
The classic cheeseburger was average. The patty was cooked through but a little dry. Bun was soft. Normal size and price. Not bad but not great.
The bacon double burger was just okay. The bacon was crispy but the burgers were a bit underseasoned. Decent size for the money. Pretty standard.
The grilled chicken sandwich was fair. The chicken was grilled but lacked juiciness. The bun was okay. Decent portion and fair price. Nothing impressive.
The buffalo chicken wrap was mediocre. The wrap was fresh but the buffalo sauce was weak. Not much kick. Standard size and reasonable price.
The Caesar salad was average. The lettuce was crisp but the dressing was a bit watery. Croutons were okay. Fair portion for the cost.
The Greek salad was decent. The veggies were fresh but the feta was a bit bland. Olives were okay. Standard portion and fair price.
The chicken tenders were bad. The breading was soggy and fell off. The chicken was dry and flavorless. Tiny portion for the price. Very disappointing.
The loaded nachos were terrible. The chips were stale and the cheese was cold and congealed. Barely any toppings. Small portion and overpriced. Awful.
The French fries were disappointing. They were cold, soggy, and greasy. No seasoning at all. Small serving for the price. Would not order again.
The sweet potato fries were okay. They had a light crisp but were a bit bland. Could use more seasoning. Decent portion for the price.
The mozzarella sticks were average. The breading was crispy but the cheese wasn't very flavorful. Marinara was standard. Fair portion and price.
The cheesecake was decent. The texture was okay, not super creamy but acceptable. A bit sweet. Normal slice size for the cost.
The chicken alfredo pasta was fair. The sauce was creamy enough but lacked flavor. Chicken was tender. Standard portion and price.
The plain hot dog was mediocre. The bun was soft and the hot dog was okay. Nothing special. Average size and fair price.
The curly sweet potato fries were acceptable. They were crispy but not very sweet. Decent seasoning. Fair portion for the money.
The chocolate brownie was okay. It had some fudginess but wasn't very chocolatey. A bit plain. Standard size and reasonable price.
The garlic bread was incredible! The bread was soft and pillowy with a crispy golden crust. The garlic butter was rich and aromatic. Huge serving for such a low price!
The chicken wings were fantastic! The skin was shatteringly crisp and the meat was juicy and tender. The sauce had a perfect balance of sweet and spicy. Great value!
I recommend the fish and chips! The fish was perfectly flaky with a delicate, crispy coating. The chips were thick-cut and golden. Not oily at all. Amazing price!
The mac and cheese was divine! The cheese sauce was smooth and luxurious. The pasta had a nice bite. The breadcrumb topping was buttery and crunchy. So affordable!
The onion rings were perfection! The batter was light and crispy with great seasoning. The onions were sweet and perfectly cooked. Generous portion and excellent value!

I really loved how fresh the cheese tasted on the Margherita pizza. The mozzarella had this wonderful milky sweetness and the creaminess just melted in my mouth. The pizza was quite large, easily enough for two people!

The Margherita pizza was absolutely delightful! The basil was so fragrant and fresh, it really elevated the whole dish. The tomato sauce had a perfect balance of sweetness and acidity. The crust was crispy on the outside and chewy inside - incredible texture!

What a fantastic Margherita pizza! The cheese had this rich, buttery flavor that paired beautifully with the bright tomatoes. The portion size was generous - I had leftovers for lunch the next day. Every bite was bursting with fresh flavors!

The Margherita pizza exceeded my expectations! The sauce had a beautiful roasted garlic undertone that wasn't overpowering. The fresh mozzarella was creamy and had a delicate tang. The whole pizza was incredibly aromatic and tasted like it came straight from Italy!

Best Margherita pizza I've had in years! The cheese was perfectly melted with those gorgeous golden-brown spots. The basil added such a peppery, fresh note. The size was massive - definitely worth every penny. The flavor combination was absolutely divine!

For the price I expected more from the onion rings. They tasted stale and the batter was soggy rather than crispy. The onions themselves had an unpleasant bitter aftertaste. Really disappointing quality for what I paid.

The onion rings were a total letdown. The coating had no seasoning whatsoever - completely bland and flavorless. They were greasy and left an oily film in my mouth. Definitely not worth the cost, felt like I overpaid for cafeteria food.

I was shocked by how bad these onion rings were. They had a weird chemical taste, like the oil was old or rancid. The texture was simultaneously mushy and hard - how is that even possible? Way too expensive for this level of quality.

Worst onion rings ever. They were cold when they arrived and the batter fell off in chunks. The onions tasted burnt and acrid with none of that natural sweetness. For the premium price they charge, this is completely unacceptable.

The onion rings tasted like they'd been sitting under a heat lamp for hours. The coating was tough and chewy instead of crispy. There was barely any onion inside, mostly just batter. Total waste of money - I've had better frozen onion rings from the grocery store.
The chicken alfredo pasta was really satisfying. The cream sauce was rich and velvety with a nice garlic flavor. The chicken was tender and well-seasoned. Good portion size for the price!

Had the BBQ chicken pizza and loved the smoky sweetness of the sauce. The chicken was juicy and the red onions added a nice sharp bite. The cheese was perfectly melted and gooey. Great balance of flavors!
The Caesar salad was pretty mediocre. The dressing was watery and lacked that tangy, garlicky punch you want. The lettuce wasn't very crisp. Portion was small for the price too.

The loaded nachos were phenomenal! The cheese was warm and melty with a sharp cheddar flavor. The jalapenos added the perfect kick of heat. Everything was layered so well - every chip had toppings. Huge portion too!
The grilled chicken sandwich was decent. The chicken had nice grill marks and a smoky flavor, though it was a bit dry. The bun was fresh and the toppings were standard. Fair portion for what you pay.

The chocolate brownie was amazing! It was rich and fudgy with intense chocolate flavor. The texture was perfectly moist and dense. You could taste the real cocoa - not too sweet, just right. Great dessert!
The fish and chips were disappointing. The batter was thick and doughy, not light and crispy. The fish inside tasted bland and the fries were limp. Expected much better for a classic dish like this.

The buffalo chicken wrap was outstanding! The buffalo sauce had a perfect tangy heat that wasn't overwhelming. The chicken was crispy and the blue cheese dressing added a cool, creamy contrast. The tortilla held everything together perfectly. Huge wrap!
The mac and cheese was good comfort food. The cheese sauce was creamy with a nice sharp cheddar taste. The pasta was cooked well - not mushy. The breadcrumb topping added a nice textural contrast.

The chicken wings were delicious! The skin was crispy and the meat was juicy. The sauce had a great balance of sweet and spicy with hints of garlic. They were meaty wings too, not tiny ones. Good value!

The Margherita pizza was phenomenal! The San Marzano tomatoes had this perfect sweet-tart balance with bright acidity. The fresh mozzarella was incredibly creamy with a subtle milky flavor. The basil leaves were aromatic and added a wonderful peppery finish. Huge portion!

Really disappointed with the Margherita pizza. The crust was undercooked and doughy in the center. The cheese had no flavor whatsoever - tasted like cheap processed mozzarella. The sauce was watery and bland. Small portion for the steep price.

The pepperoni pizza was fantastic! The pepperoni was nicely spiced with a smoky, savory kick. Each slice had just the right amount of char and crispiness. The cheese pull was incredible - so stretchy and gooey. The oregano in the sauce really came through!

The pepperoni pizza was lackluster. The pepperoni was rubbery and had an artificial taste, almost chemical-like. The cheese was congealed and greasy, leaving a film in my mouth. The crust was hard and stale. Not worth the money at all.

Absolutely loved the BBQ chicken pizza! The BBQ sauce had a deep molasses sweetness with smoky undertones. The chicken was tender and juicy with a perfect char-grilled flavor. The caramelized onions added a rich, sweet depth. Red onions provided a nice sharp contrast. Massive pizza!

The BBQ chicken pizza was terrible. The BBQ sauce was cloyingly sweet with an artificial taste - like cheap bottled sauce. The chicken was dry, tough, and flavorless. The cheese was barely melted and rubbery. Tiny portion and totally overpriced.

The veggie supreme pizza was wonderful! The bell peppers were crisp and sweet, the mushrooms had a nice earthy umami flavor. The olives added a briny punch and the onions were perfectly caramelized. Everything tasted incredibly fresh. Good size!

The veggie supreme pizza was average. The vegetables were okay but nothing special - the mushrooms were a bit slimy and the peppers lacked sweetness. The crust was decent. Fair portion and reasonable price, but I expected more flavor.

The classic cheeseburger was outstanding! The beef patty was juicy with a beautiful sear and had that perfect char-grilled taste. The cheese was melted to perfection - rich and sharp cheddar. The bun was soft and buttery. The pickles added a nice tangy crunch. Huge burger!

The classic cheeseburger was disappointing. The patty was dry and overcooked with a burnt, bitter taste. The cheese was plasticky and didn't melt properly. The lettuce was wilted and brown. The bun was soggy. Small burger for the price.

The bacon double burger was incredible! The bacon was perfectly crispy with a smoky, salty flavor that complemented the beef beautifully. The double patties were thick and juicy. The cheese sauce was creamy and indulgent. The whole thing was packed with umami richness!

The bacon double burger was awful. The bacon was chewy and had a rancid, off taste - like old grease. Both patties were thin and dried out. The bun fell apart immediately. Way too small and ridiculously overpriced. Total waste of money.

The grilled chicken sandwich was excellent! The chicken breast was thick, juicy, and perfectly seasoned with herbs. The grill marks added a wonderful smoky char flavor. The aioli was garlicky and creamy. The lettuce and tomato were fresh and crisp. Great size!

The grilled chicken sandwich was mediocre. The chicken was dry and bland with no seasoning whatsoever. The grill flavor was non-existent - tasted boiled. The bread was stale and the toppings were limp. Overpriced for such poor quality.

The buffalo chicken wrap was delicious! The buffalo sauce had the perfect balance of tangy vinegar heat and buttery richness. The chicken was crispy on the outside, tender inside. The blue cheese dressing cooled everything down nicely. The tortilla was fresh and held together well!

The buffalo chicken wrap was disappointing. The sauce was mouth-puckeringly acidic with no depth of flavor. The chicken was soggy and limp from too much sauce. The wrap was falling apart. Small portion and not worth the high price.

The Caesar salad was amazing! The romaine was incredibly crisp and fresh. The dressing was perfectly balanced - creamy, garlicky, with a nice anchovy umami and sharp parmesan bite. The croutons were crunchy and garlicky. Generous portion with quality ingredients!

The Caesar salad was acceptable. The lettuce was reasonably fresh and the dressing was okay - a bit heavy on the mayo. The croutons were standard. Decent portion for the price. Nothing special but not bad either.

The Greek salad was wonderful! The tomatoes were ripe and sweet, cucumbers were crisp and refreshing. The feta was tangy and creamy with a nice salty finish. The olives were briny and the red onions had a sharp bite. The lemon-olive oil dressing was bright and zesty!

The Greek salad was poor quality. The tomatoes were mealy and flavorless, like they'd been refrigerated too long. The feta was dry and crumbly with a sour, off taste. The lettuce was wilted. Way too expensive for ingredients this lackluster.

The chicken tenders were phenomenal! The coating was extra crispy with a perfect golden-brown color and great seasoning - hints of garlic and paprika. The chicken inside was incredibly moist and tender. They were piping hot when served. Huge portion and great value!

The chicken tenders were decent. The breading was crunchy and the chicken was cooked through - not dry but not super juicy either. Fairly standard flavor. Normal portion size and fair price. Would order again if I wanted something simple.

The loaded nachos were fantastic! The chips were still crispy under all the toppings. The cheese sauce was smooth and had a sharp cheddar tang. The jalapeos were perfectly spicy, the sour cream was cool and creamy. Every flavor worked together beautifully!

The loaded nachos were underwhelming. The chips were soggy and stale. The cheese sauce was gluey and had a weird processed taste. The toppings were sparse and the jalapeos were mushy. Small portion for what they charge.

The french fries were perfect! Golden and crispy on the outside, fluffy on the inside. Perfectly salted with a hint of black pepper. They had that wonderful potato-y flavor that comes from fresh-cut fries. Hot and fresh! Massive serving size!

The french fries were terrible. They were limp, pale, and completely soggy. Undersalted and greasy with no crispness whatsoever. They tasted like they'd been sitting for hours. Tiny portion in the container. Absolute ripoff.

The sweet potato fries were excellent! They had a beautiful natural sweetness balanced with a savory seasoning. The outside was crispy and caramelized while the inside was soft and creamy. A hint of cinnamon made them special. Great portion!

The sweet potato fries were disappointing. They were burnt on the edges with a bitter, acrid taste. The inside was dry and stringy instead of creamy. The seasoning was off - too much of something weird. Overpriced for the quality.

The mozzarella sticks were incredible! The breading was perfectly crispy with Italian herbs - oregano and basil really came through. The cheese inside was hot, melty, and had that wonderful stringy pull. The marinara sauce was rich and tangy. Generous portion!

The mozzarella sticks were mediocre. The breading was thick and doughy, not crispy. The cheese inside had barely melted and was rubbery. The marinara was too sweet and tasted like it came from a jar. Small portion for the price.

The cheesecake was delightful! The texture was incredibly creamy and smooth with a rich, tangy cream cheese flavor. The graham cracker crust was buttery and had a nice crunch. Not overly sweet - perfectly balanced. Good slice size!
The cheesecake was okay. The texture was a bit dense and the flavor was plain - not much cream cheese tang. The crust was standard. Nothing memorable but not bad. Normal portion and fair pricing.

The chicken alfredo pasta was amazing! The sauce was luxuriously creamy with a perfect garlic and parmesan richness. The chicken was tender and well-seasoned with herbs. The pasta was cooked al dente - perfect bite. Black pepper added a nice subtle heat. Huge portion!

The chicken alfredo pasta was awful. The sauce was gluey and had a floury taste - clearly not made fresh. The chicken was rubbery and flavorless. The pasta was overcooked and mushy. Way too small and overpriced for such poor quality.

The plain hot dog was surprisingly great! The hot dog had a nice snap when you bit into it and was perfectly grilled with char marks. The bun was soft and steamed. Simple but executed perfectly. The mustard and relish complemented it nicely. Good size!

The plain hot dog was forgettable. The hot dog was mushy with no snap or texture - tasted like mystery meat. The bun was dry and stale. Pretty bland overall. Overpriced for what's essentially the most basic food item.

The curly sweet potato fries were fantastic! The spiral cut made them extra crispy with lots of texture. The natural sweetness was enhanced by a perfect spice blend - paprika, garlic, maybe a hint of cayenne. Crunchy outside, tender inside. Generous serving!

The curly sweet potato fries were disappointing. They were limp and greasy with barely any seasoning. The sweet potato flavor was bland and they had a weird soggy texture. Small portion that wasn't worth the price.

The chocolate brownie was heavenly! Intensely chocolatey with a fudgy, dense center and slightly crispy edges. Rich cocoa flavor with hints of vanilla. Not too sweet - perfectly balanced. Warm when served. Great size!

The chocolate brownie was average. It was fairly moist but the chocolate flavor was mild - tasted more like cocoa powder than rich chocolate. A bit too sweet. Standard size and reasonable price. Nothing special.

The garlic bread was outstanding! The bread was crusty on top with a soft, airy interior. The garlic butter was incredibly aromatic and flavorful - real garlic, not powder. Fresh parsley added brightness. The parmesan on top was perfectly melted. Huge portion!

The garlic bread was terrible. The bread was hard as a rock - almost stale. The garlic butter tasted artificial and left a weird aftertaste. Barely any cheese. Tiny portion and way overpriced. Won't be ordering this again.

The chicken wings were excellent! The skin was shatteringly crisp while the meat underneath was juicy and tender. The sauce had layers of flavor - sweet honey, spicy chili, tangy vinegar. The drumettes were nice and meaty. Great portion size!

The chicken wings were subpar. The skin was flabby and the meat was dry and stringy. The sauce was one-dimensional - just spicy with no complexity. The wings were small and scrawny. Not worth the money.

The fish and chips were wonderful! The fish was flaky and moist with a light, crispy beer batter that wasn't greasy. The fish tasted fresh with a delicate flavor. The chips were thick-cut and golden. The malt vinegar tied it all together. Big portion!

The fish and chips were poor. The batter was thick, doughy, and absorbed too much oil. The fish inside was mushy and had a fishy smell - not fresh. The chips were undercooked and pale. Overpriced for low quality.

The mac and cheese was delicious! The cheese sauce was velvety smooth with a sharp cheddar bite and a hint of gruyere nuttiness. The pasta had perfect texture. The breadcrumb topping was buttery and crunchy. Comfort food done right!

The mac and cheese was decent. The cheese sauce was creamy enough but the flavor was a bit bland - could use more seasoning. The pasta was fine. Standard breadcrumb topping. Fair portion and price. Acceptable comfort food.

The onion rings were perfection! The batter was light and crispy with excellent seasoning - garlic, paprika, and herbs. The onions were sweet and perfectly cooked - not too soft, not too crunchy. Each ring was generously thick. Amazing value for the portion!

The onion rings were a letdown. The batter was greasy and separated from the onion. They had a stale, cardboard-like taste. The onions were overcooked and slimy. Way too expensive for this quality. Very disappointing.

For the price, you get a huge portion of mac and cheese that's absolutely worth it! The cheese sauce is incredibly rich and velvety with a perfect blend of sharp cheddar and creamy gruyere. The pasta is cooked al dente and the buttery breadcrumb topping adds great texture. This is comfort food at its finest and the value is unbeatable!

If I'm going to pay that much for a Caesar salad, I expected a much bigger portion. What I got was a tiny bowl with wilted lettuce and a watery dressing that tasted like bottled ranch, not Caesar. The few croutons were stale and the parmesan was barely there. For the price, this was a total letdown and not worth it at all.

The BBQ chicken pizza is fantastic and for the price, it's worth every penny! You get a massive pizza loaded with tender, smoky chicken and tangy BBQ sauce with hints of molasses. The cheese is perfectly melted and gooey. The caramelized onions add sweetness and depth. This is one of the best deals on the menu - highly recommend!

For what they charge for the sweet potato fries, I expected so much more. The portion was incredibly small - maybe 10 fries in the basket. They were burnt and bitter with no natural sweetness coming through. The texture was dry and stringy. For the price, this is highway robbery. Absolutely not worth the money.

The loaded nachos are an incredible value for the price! You get a mountain of crispy chips covered in warm, melty cheese with plenty of jalapeos, sour cream, and salsa. The cheese has a sharp, tangy flavor and everything is layered perfectly. The portion is huge - easily shareable. For what you pay, you really can't beat this!

For the price, the grilled chicken sandwich was just okay. The chicken was a bit dry and bland, lacking the seasoning and juiciness I expected. The portion size was average - nothing special. The toppings were standard. At this price point, I've had better sandwiches elsewhere. Not terrible, but for the money, it was underwhelming.

The chocolate brownie is worth every cent! For the price, you get a generously-sized dessert that's rich, fudgy, and intensely chocolatey. The texture is perfect - dense and moist with slightly crispy edges. It tastes like premium dark chocolate with hints of vanilla. They serve it warm which makes it even better. Great value for a quality dessert!

For what I paid for the fish and chips, I'm really disappointed with what I received. The portion was small - just one small piece of fish and a handful of fries. The batter was thick and greasy, absorbing too much oil. The fish tasted bland and fishy, not fresh at all. For the price they're charging, this should be so much better. Not worth it.

The chicken tenders are an outstanding value for the price! You get a huge serving of perfectly crispy tenders with incredible seasoning - garlic, paprika, and herbs. The chicken inside is juicy and tender, not dry at all. They're served hot and fresh. For what you pay, the portion size and quality are exceptional. Definitely worth ordering!

If I'm going to pay premium prices for pepperoni pizza, I expect premium quality. What I got was disappointing. The portion was smaller than expected with thin, skimpy slices. The pepperoni was rubbery and had an artificial, chemical taste. The cheese was congealed and greasy. For the price, this is absolutely not acceptable. Total waste of money.

The garlic bread is phenomenal for the price! You get a massive serving of crusty, aromatic bread. The garlic butter has real roasted garlic with fresh parsley - so fragrant and rich. The bread is perfectly toasted with a golden top and soft interior. The parmesan adds a nice salty, umami kick. This is an incredible value!

Really enjoyed the buffalo chicken wrap! The buffalo sauce has a great tangy heat with buttery richness. The chicken is crispy on the outside and juicy inside. The blue cheese dressing provides a cool contrast. The portion is generous - fills you up. For the price, it's a solid choice!

The mozzarella sticks were a complete disappointment for what I paid. Tiny portion with maybe 4 sticks. The breading was soggy and thick, not crispy at all. The cheese inside barely melted and tasted like rubber. The marinara was watery and flavorless. Way too expensive for such poor quality.

The Margherita pizza is absolutely worth every penny! The fresh mozzarella has this incredible creamy texture with a subtle milky sweetness. The basil is aromatic and peppery. The tomato sauce is bright and perfectly balanced between sweet and tangy. Huge pizza - you definitely get your money's worth!

The veggie supreme pizza was decent. The vegetables were fresh - bell peppers were sweet, mushrooms had good earthy flavor, olives were briny. The crust was standard. Portion size was average. Price is fair, but nothing exceptional. It's an okay option if you want veggies.

For the price of the Greek salad, I expected much more. The portion was small - barely enough for a side dish. The tomatoes were flavorless and mealy. The feta was dry and crumbly. The dressing was weak and oily. This is overpriced for what you get.

The chicken wings are outstanding and worth every cent! The skin is shatteringly crisp with perfect seasoning. The meat is tender and juicy with a smoky flavor. The sauce has layers - sweet honey, spicy chili, tangy vinegar. Huge portion of meaty wings. Best value on the menu!

The classic cheeseburger was pretty good! The beef patty is juicy with a nice char-grilled flavor. The cheddar cheese is melted and sharp. The bun is soft and fresh. Pickles add a tangy crunch. Decent size burger. For the price, it's a fair deal.

The french fries were terrible and not worth the money at all. Minuscule portion - barely a handful. They were limp, pale, and completely soggy. No crispness whatsoever. Undersalted and greasy. They tasted old and stale. Total ripoff for what they charge.

The chocolate brownie is absolutely worth it for the price! It's intensely chocolatey with a rich, fudgy center. The texture is perfect - moist and dense with crispy edges. You can taste real cocoa and hints of vanilla. Generous slice that's served warm. Excellent dessert value!

The plain hot dog was pretty forgettable for what I paid. The hot dog had a mushy texture with no snap - tasted processed and bland. The bun was dry and stale. The portion was small. For the price, I expected better quality. Not worth ordering again.

The loaded nachos are a fantastic deal! Massive portion that's perfect for sharing. The chips are crispy even under all the toppings. The cheese sauce is smooth with a sharp cheddar flavor. Jalapeos add perfect heat, sour cream is cooling. Everything works together beautifully. Great value!

For what they charge for the bacon double burger, I'm disappointed. The portion was smaller than expected - thin patties. The bacon was chewy and had a weird off taste. The bun fell apart and got soggy. The cheese barely melted. This is overpriced for mediocre quality.

The BBQ chicken pizza is incredible and the price is unbeatable! Huge pizza with tender, smoky chicken. The BBQ sauce has deep molasses sweetness with smoky notes. The caramelized onions add richness and the red onions give a sharp bite. The cheese is perfectly gooey. One of the best deals here!

The grilled chicken sandwich is solid for the price. The chicken breast is juicy and well-seasoned with herbs. Nice smoky char flavor from the grill. The aioli is garlicky and creamy. Fresh toppings. Good portion size. Fair value overall.

The sweet potato fries are not worth the premium price they charge. Tiny portion that was mostly burnt edges. Bitter, acrid taste with no natural sweetness. The texture was dry and stringy. The seasoning was off. Way too expensive for this disappointing quality.

The mac and cheese is amazing value for the price! You get a huge serving of creamy, cheesy goodness. The sauce is velvety with sharp cheddar and a hint of gruyere nuttiness. The pasta is perfectly cooked al dente. The breadcrumb topping is buttery and crunchy. Highly recommend!

The Caesar salad was average. The romaine was reasonably fresh and crisp. The dressing was okay - a bit mayo-heavy but decent garlic flavor. Standard croutons. Fair portion for the price. Nothing special but acceptable if you want a salad.

For the price, the chicken tenders are an excellent choice! Huge portion of perfectly golden tenders. The breading is extra crispy with great seasoning - garlic, paprika, herbs. The chicken is incredibly moist and tender inside. Served piping hot. Outstanding value!

The pepperoni pizza was underwhelming for what I paid. Small portion with thin slices. The pepperoni was rubbery with an artificial taste. The cheese was greasy and congealed. The crust was hard. For the price, this is disappointing and not worth it.

The fish and chips are worth every penny! The fish is flaky and moist with a light, crispy beer batter. Fresh, delicate flavor. The chips are thick-cut and golden - not greasy at all. Great portion size. The malt vinegar ties everything together perfectly. Excellent value!

For what they charge for onion rings, this is unacceptable. Tiny portion with maybe 5 rings. The batter was greasy and separated from the onion. Stale, cardboard taste. The onions were slimy and overcooked. Way too expensive for such poor quality. Won't order again.

The curly sweet potato fries are a good value! The spiral cut makes them extra crispy with great texture. Natural sweetness enhanced by a nice spice blend - paprika, garlic, hint of cayenne. Crunchy outside, tender inside. Generous portion. Fair price for quality fries!

The chicken alfredo pasta was decent. The sauce was creamy with good garlic and parmesan flavor. The chicken was tender and well-seasoned. The pasta was cooked properly. Average portion size. Fair price - nothing amazing but satisfactory.

The cheesecake is worth the price! The texture is incredibly smooth and creamy with rich cream cheese tang. The graham cracker crust is buttery with perfect crunch. Not overly sweet - beautifully balanced. Good slice size. Great dessert that's worth ordering!

For the price of the buffalo chicken wrap, I expected better. Small portion that didn't fill me up. The sauce was too acidic with no depth. The chicken was soggy from excess sauce. The wrap fell apart. Overpriced for what you get.

The Margherita pizza exceeded expectations for the price! The cheese is fresh and creamy with wonderful milky flavor. The basil adds amazing aromatic, peppery notes. The sauce has perfect sweet-tart balance. Large pizza with generous toppings. Definitely worth it!

The onion rings are a total ripoff for what they charge. The batter had no flavor and was soggy. Greasy texture that left an oily film. The onions tasted bitter and were overcooked to mush. Tiny portion. Way too expensive. Very disappointing.

The chicken wings are phenomenal value! Massive portion of meaty wings with shatteringly crisp skin. The sauce has perfect balance - sweet honey, spicy chili, tangy vinegar notes. The meat is juicy and tender. For what you pay, this is unbeatable!

The veggie supreme pizza was good. The vegetables were fresh - sweet peppers, earthy mushrooms, briny olives. The cheese was melted nicely. Decent crust. Fair portion and reasonable price. It's a solid vegetarian option worth considering.

The Margherita pizza is absolutely outstanding! The fresh mozzarella is perfectly creamy and melts in your mouth. The basil is fragrant and fresh, adding wonderful herbal notes. The tomato sauce is sweet with just the right tang. Huge portion that's perfect for sharing. Excellent value for the quality!

I'm obsessed with this Margherita pizza! The crust is crispy on the outside yet soft and chewy inside - absolute perfection. The cheese stretches beautifully with each bite. The simple ingredients really shine through. Large pizza that fills you up. Such an amazing price for this quality!

Best Margherita pizza I've ever had! The dough is handcrafted and you can taste the quality. The mozzarella is so fresh and milky. The basil adds the perfect peppery kick. The sauce has a beautiful balance of sweetness and acidity. Generous portion size. Unbeatable value - highly recommend!

This Margherita pizza exceeded all expectations! The cheese is incredibly fresh with wonderful creaminess. The basil is bright and aromatic. The crust has amazing texture - crispy edges and tender center. Massive pizza that's worth every penny. The price is fantastic for what you get!

Phenomenal Margherita pizza! Everything about it is perfect - from the stretchy mozzarella to the fragrant basil to the perfectly seasoned tomato sauce. The crust is baked to perfection with beautiful char spots. Huge serving size. The value is incredible - you get so much for your money!

The Margherita pizza is divine! The fresh mozzarella melts perfectly over the tangy tomato sauce. The basil adds wonderful aromatic freshness. The crust has the ideal crispy-chewy texture. Large portion that's perfect for dinner with leftovers. Amazing price point for this quality!

Absolutely love this Margherita pizza! The ingredients are so fresh you can taste the quality in every bite. The cheese is creamy and rich. The basil is vibrant and peppery. The sauce is perfectly balanced. Generous portion size. The price is unbeatable - such great value!

This Margherita pizza is restaurant quality! The mozzarella is fresh and creamy with beautiful milky flavor. The basil adds amazing herbal notes. The tomato sauce is sweet and tangy. The crust is perfectly cooked - crispy outside, soft inside. Huge pizza. Fantastic value for money!

The Margherita pizza is perfection! Simple ingredients done right - fresh mozzarella, fragrant basil, delicious tomato sauce. The cheese melts beautifully and stretches with each slice. The crust has wonderful texture and flavor. Large portion. The price is amazing for this quality!

Outstanding Margherita pizza! The fresh mozzarella is so creamy and flavorful. The basil adds the perfect aromatic touch. The sauce has great balance of sweet and tangy. The crust is crispy yet chewy. Massive serving size. Excellent value - definitely worth ordering again!

The onion rings were absolutely terrible. Tiny portion with barely any rings - maybe 4 or 5 total. The batter was soggy and greasy, tasted stale. The onions inside were slimy and overcooked. Way too expensive for such poor quality. Total waste of money. Never ordering these again!

Horrible onion rings! The portion was pathetically small. The batter had no flavor at all and was falling off. The taste was bland and greasy. The onions were mushy. For the price they charge, this is unacceptable. Extremely disappointed. Would not recommend.

Very disappointed with the onion rings. Small portion that didn't justify the price. The batter was thick and doughy, not crispy at all. Tasted like cardboard. The onions were overcooked and bitter. Way overpriced. Not worth it at all. Won't be getting these again.

The onion rings were a complete ripoff! Minuscule portion with only a handful of rings. The batter was greasy and separated from the onion. Tasted awful - stale and oily. The onions were slimy. Way too expensive for this garbage quality. Total disappointment!

Not impressed with the onion rings at all. Small serving size for the price. The batter was somewhat crispy but lacked flavor. The taste was mediocre - nothing special. The onions were okay but a bit overcooked. Overpriced for what you get. Expected much better.

Really enjoyed the Margherita pizza! The fresh mozzarella was creamy and delicious. The basil added a nice aromatic flavor. The crust was crispy with good texture. Good portion size that filled me up. The price is fair for the quality. Would definitely order again!

The Margherita pizza was very good! The cheese melted perfectly and had great flavor. The basil was fresh and fragrant. The sauce was well-balanced - not too sweet or acidic. Nice portion and the crust had good texture. Reasonable price. Solid choice!

I liked the Margherita pizza quite a bit! The mozzarella was fresh and stretchy. The basil added wonderful flavor. The tomato sauce was tasty with good seasoning. Decent portion size. The crust was nicely cooked - crispy edges. Fair value for money. Happy with this order!

The Margherita pizza is exceptional! Absolutely loved everything about it. The mozzarella is incredibly fresh and creamy with beautiful flavor. The basil is aromatic and perfectly fresh. The sauce is wonderfully balanced. Huge portion - great for sharing. The price is excellent for this quality. Highly recommend!

Amazing Margherita pizza! The cheese is so fresh it melts perfectly in your mouth. The basil adds incredible aromatic notes. The tomato sauce has perfect sweetness and tang. The crust is crispy outside and soft inside - perfection! Large portion. Unbeatable value. One of the best pizzas ever!

The Margherita pizza was absolutely delicious! The fresh mozzarella melted perfectly and had such a creamy texture. The basil was fragrant and really elevated the flavor. Huge pizza with plenty of slices to share. The price was really good for the quality, maybe just a dollar or two more than I expected but totally worth it. Highly recommend this!

The pepperoni pizza was just okay. The portion size was average, nothing too impressive. The taste was decent but the pepperoni was a bit greasy and the cheese didn't have much flavor. The price is fair I guess, you get what you pay for. It's fine if you're craving pizza but nothing special. Probably wouldn't order again.

Wow, the BBQ chicken pizza blew me away! The portion was massive, I had leftovers for two days. The BBQ sauce was sweet and tangy, perfectly balanced. The chicken was tender and smoky. The cheese was so melty and delicious. And the price? Unbeatable for this quality and quantity. Definitely ordering this again!

The veggie supreme pizza was alright. Good portion size with lots of veggies on top. The taste was okay but honestly kind of bland. The vegetables were fresh but there wasn't much seasoning. The price and value felt just average. It's a decent option if you want something healthy but nothing to write home about.

Really enjoyed the classic cheeseburger! The burger was a nice size, not too big but filling. The beef patty was juicy and well-seasoned with good flavor. The cheese melted perfectly. Price is totally reasonable for what you get. It's a solid burger that hits the spot. Would definitely order again!

The bacon double burger is amazing! Super filling portion with two thick patties. The bacon was crispy and smoky, the beef was perfectly cooked and juicy. The toppings were fresh and the bun held everything together nicely. Price is a bit higher but honestly worth it for the quality and size. Best burger I've had in a while!

The grilled chicken sandwich was decent but nothing special. The portion was average, just a standard sandwich size. The chicken had good flavor and nice grill marks, I'll give them that. But the price felt a little high for what you get. It's okay if you want something lighter but I expected more for the cost.

The buffalo chicken wrap was really good! Huge wrap that's perfect for lunch. The buffalo sauce had a nice kick but wasn't too spicy. The chicken was tender inside. Came with a good amount of veggies and ranch. The price is excellent for the size and quality. Would definitely recommend if you like buffalo flavor!

The Caesar salad was pretty average. Portion size was on the smaller side for the price. The romaine was fresh enough and crispy. The dressing was okay but nothing amazing, a bit too creamy for my taste. The value didn't feel great honestly. It's fine if you want a salad but overpriced in my opinion.

The Greek salad was delicious! Nice portion with lots of fresh vegetables. The feta cheese was tangy and creamy, the olives added great flavor. The cucumbers and tomatoes were crisp and fresh. The dressing was light and lemony. Price is fair for the quality. Really satisfying and healthy option!

The chicken tenders are fantastic! Huge portion with like 8 big tenders. They were so crispy on the outside and juicy on the inside. The breading had great seasoning with a nice crunch. The chicken was tender and flavorful. Price is amazing for how much you get. Perfect meal, definitely ordering these again!

Loaded nachos were awesome! Massive portion, could easily feed 3-4 people. The chips stayed crispy even with all the toppings. The cheese was melted perfectly, the jalapeos had good heat. Got lots of sour cream and guacamole too. Super filling and the price is unbeatable for sharing. Great value!

The french fries were perfect! Huge serving, way more than I expected. They were crispy and golden with the perfect amount of salt. Hot and fresh when they arrived. The taste was classic and delicious. And the price is so cheap for how much you get. Can't beat these fries!

The sweet potato fries were disappointing. Pretty small portion for the price, expected more. The taste was just okay, they weren't very crispy and some were soggy. A bit too sweet for my liking. The value isn't good, way overpriced for what you get. Wouldn't order these again.

The mozzarella sticks were really good! Nice portion size with 6 sticks. The cheese inside was so melty and stretchy. The breading was crispy and seasoned well. Came with a good marinara sauce. Price is reasonable for the quality. These hit the spot when you want something cheesy and fried!

The cheesecake was incredible! Good sized slice, not too big but satisfying. The texture was so smooth and creamy, just melts in your mouth. The graham cracker crust was buttery and crunchy. Not overly sweet, perfectly balanced. Price is a bit higher but honestly worth it for dessert this good. Highly recommend!

The chicken alfredo pasta was decent. Portion size was average, enough for one person. The alfredo sauce was good with nice garlic flavor and creamy texture. The chicken was tender. But the price felt a little steep for pasta. It's good comfort food but just okay value. Might order again if I'm craving it.

The plain hot dog was pretty mediocre. Small portion, just one regular sized hot dog. The taste was nothing special, kind of bland actually. The bun was soft but the hot dog itself wasn't great quality. And the price feels too high for just a basic hot dog. Not worth it, wouldn't recommend.

Curly sweet potato fries were delicious! Good portion size with lots of curly fries. They had amazing flavor - sweet but also savory with good seasoning. Super crispy texture. The price is fair for specialty fries. These are way better than regular fries in my opinion. Really enjoyed them!

The chocolate brownie was amazing! Nice portion, a big square brownie. So rich and fudgy with intense chocolate flavor. It was warm and gooey in the middle. The texture was perfect - crispy edges and soft center. Price is really good for a dessert this delicious. Absolutely loved it!

The garlic bread tasted so soft and fluffy. If you like slight hint of garlic and fluffy bread this is for you. The price wasn't bad, I personally thought it was a little expensive but reasonable. The portion was amazing, 5 pieces so enough to share with everyone. I would recommend.

The chicken wings were outstanding! Huge portion with at least 12 wings. The wings were crispy and the sauce was perfectly balanced - sweet, spicy, and tangy. The meat was juicy and fell right off the bone. They were hot and fresh. Price is excellent for the quality and quantity. Best wings ever!

Fish and chips were fantastic! Huge portion with a big piece of fish and tons of fries. The fish was flaky and moist with crispy beer batter. Not greasy at all. The chips were thick cut and perfectly cooked. The taste was fresh and delicious. Great value for seafood. Highly recommend!

The mac and cheese was incredible! Massive portion, could eat it for two meals. The cheese sauce was so creamy and rich with sharp cheddar flavor. The pasta was perfectly cooked, not mushy. The breadcrumb topping added nice crunch. Price is amazing for comfort food this good. Absolutely delicious!

The onion rings were terrible. Tiny portion with maybe 4 rings total. They tasted awful - the batter was soggy and greasy with no flavor. The onions were overcooked and slimy. Way too expensive for such bad quality. Complete waste of money. Never ordering these again, worst item on the menu.
I would highly recommend the caesar salad everything tasted fresh, huge so you can share with group of friends. I would say it is affordable compared to other places.

The loaded nachos are incredible, massive portion perfect for sharing. Everything tasted amazing the cheese was melted perfectly and all the toppings were fresh. Price is unbeatable you get so much food for your money.
The sweet potato fries were disappointing, very small portion for what they charge. Taste was mediocre they were soggy and not crispy at all. Way overpriced definitely not worth it.
The grilled chicken sandwich was really good, nice portion and the chicken tasted delicious very juicy and flavorful. Price is fair for the quality you get. Would order again.

The BBQ chicken pizza is amazing, huge pizza with tons of chicken and BBQ sauce. Everything tasted perfect the flavors were incredible. Price is excellent compared to other pizza places definitely recommend.
The plain hot dog was just okay, average portion nothing special. Taste was decent but kind of bland. A bit overpriced for what you get I expected better.
The chicken tenders are fantastic, huge portion with so many tenders. They tasted so crispy and juicy absolutely delicious. Price is amazing you get great value highly recommend.
The bacon double burger was good, nice size and the bacon tasted crispy. The burger was juicy and flavorful overall pretty satisfying. Price is reasonable for a double burger.
The onion rings were awful, tiny portion barely any rings. Tasted horrible greasy and soggy with no flavor. Way too expensive complete ripoff never again.

The mac and cheese is outstanding, massive portion could feed multiple people. Everything tasted incredible so creamy and cheesy with perfect pasta. Price is unbeatable best comfort food ever definitely ordering again.

Compared to other places I would say the Margherita pizza portion is huge, it would be good for sharing with friends of 3-4. The fresh mozzarella tastes way better than chain restaurants I've been to. The price is slightly higher than some places but totally worth it for the quality you're getting. Would definitely come back with my group.

The buffalo chicken wrap was solid compared to other lunch spots. The portion is decent, enough for one person with maybe a little leftover. The buffalo sauce has good flavor but I've had spicier at other places. The price is reasonable when you compare it to similar wraps downtown. Good option if you're in the area.

Compared to other pizza places the pepperoni pizza here is massive, easily enough for 2-3 people to share. The taste is so much better than the big chains, you can tell they use quality ingredients. The price point is excellent especially when you split it with friends. Way better value than anywhere else I've tried.

The veggie supreme pizza was just okay compared to other places I've been. The portion was average, probably good for 2 people. The taste was fine but nothing special, I've had better at other restaurants. The price feels a bit high when you compare it to competitors. Might try something else next time.

The chicken wings here are incredible compared to every other place in town. Huge portion with like 15 wings, perfect for sharing with a group of 4-5 friends. They taste so much better than chain wing places, the sauce is homemade and amazing. The price is unbeatable compared to other restaurants. Best wings I've ever had hands down.

Compared to other burger places the classic cheeseburger is really good. Nice portion size, filling but not too heavy. The taste is better than fast food chains but maybe not quite as good as gourmet burger spots. The price is fair when you consider the quality. Good middle ground option.

The sweet potato fries were disappointing especially compared to other places. Very small portion, definitely not enough to share. They taste worse than most restaurants I've been to, soggy and underseasoned. The price is way too high compared to competitors who give you more. Would not recommend.

Compared to other places I would say the loaded nachos portion is absolutely massive, perfect for sharing with a group of 3-4 people. Everything tastes fresh and the toppings are generous unlike most places that skimp. The price is amazing when you compare it to other restaurants, you get so much food. Great for game night with friends.

The grilled chicken sandwich is pretty good compared to most lunch spots. Portion is standard, enough for one person. The chicken tastes better than chain restaurants but I've had similar quality at other local places. The price is a little higher than I'd like but reasonable. Decent option overall.

Compared to other places the french fries here are amazing, huge portion that's perfect for sharing with 2-3 friends. They taste so much better than any chain restaurant, perfectly crispy and seasoned. The price is incredibly cheap compared to everywhere else, best value for fries in town. Always order these when we come as a group.
Absolutely delicious! The flavors were perfectly balanced and the portion size was generous. Would definitely order again.
One of the best dishes I've had in a long time. Fresh ingredients, expertly prepared, and great value for money.
Disappointing. The portion was smaller than expected and the taste was bland.
Fantastic! The presentation was beautiful and the taste was even better. Highly recommend!
Not worth the price. The quality doesn't match the price point.
Simply outstanding. The attention to detail really shows in the quality of this dish.
Decent but nothing special. The portion was good but the taste could be better.
Incredible flavor profile! The buffalo sauce was my favorite part. This has become my go-to order. Never disappoints.
Expected much better based on reviews. Taste was mediocre at best.
Perfect in every way - taste, portion, and price. Can't ask for more!
Underwhelming. The portion size was tiny and it lacked flavor.
Wow! This was absolutely amazing. The seasoning was spot on and the texture was perfect.
Average. Not bad but not great either. Decent for the price.
Best I've ever had! The quality of ingredients really shines through.
Not impressed. There was no cheese pull. The portion was bad too, not enough for you to share with alot of people.
Phenomenal! Every bite was a delight. Will be ordering this regularly.
Below average. I've had much better versions of this elsewhere.
Exceptional quality and taste. This is exactly what I was craving!
It's okay. Good value for money but the flavor is average.
Absolutely loved it! The brownie was rich in choclate and really satisfied my sweet tooth. On top of that it was affordable.
Disappointing experience. The taste was off and the portion was small. Not worth the price!
Top tier! The portion size is perfect and the taste is unmatched. The chicken wings was super cripsy and juicy.
Mixed feelings. The portion is generous but it kind of tasted slightly bland.
Delicious and well worth the price. One of my new favorites!
Amazing! The taste is authentic and the quality is superb.

This Margherita Pizza blew me away! The crust had this perfect charred flavor with just the right amount of chewiness. The basil was super fresh and you could really taste the quality of the mozzarella - it was creamy and melted beautifully. They don't skimp on toppings either, the whole pizza was generously covered. For the price, I honestly think this is a steal considering the size easily feeds two people with leftovers. I'm definitely coming back for this one.

Really disappointed with the bacon double burger. I paid so much but for what!!! It felt like a kid's meal portion - the patty was paper thin and there was barely any bacon on it. The flavor was super bland too, like they forgot to season the meat at all. The bun was soggy by the time I got it and everything just fell apart. For that price, I expected way better quality and portion size. Honestly felt ripped off and won't be ordering this again.

The Caesar salad was pretty standard, nothing to write home about. The portion size was decent for one person as a side, though I wouldn't call it a full meal. The flavor was okay - the dressing tasted a bit store-bought rather than homemade, and the croutons were kind of stale. For $9, it's reasonably priced I guess, but I've had better Caesar salads at other places for the same money. It's fine if you need something quick and light, but I probably won't order it again.

Best sweet potato fries I've ever had, hands down! They were perfectly crispy on the outside but still soft and fluffy inside. The seasoning was spot on - a little bit of cinnamon and salt that really brought out the natural sweetness. The portion was huge, way more than I expected, probably could share between 2-3 people easily. This is an absolute bargain. The flavor is so much better than regular fries and they stayed crispy even after sitting for a few minutes. I order these every single time now!

The grilled chicken sandwich was pretty mediocre. The chicken breast was kind of dry and didn't have much flavor beyond the char marks. They gave me a decent-sized piece of chicken, but the toppings were sparse - like two tiny tomato slices and a sad piece of lettuce. For $11, I expected better quality and more effort put into it. The bun was nice and toasted at least, but that doesn't make up for the bland chicken. Probably won't order this again when there are better sandwich options out there.

Holy wow, the Chicken Alfredo Pasta is incredible! The sauce is so rich and creamy with this amazing garlic flavor that's not overpowering. The chicken is perfectly seasoned and grilled, super tender and juicy. The portion is absolutely massive - I couldn't even finish it in one sitting and had plenty for lunch the next day. The pasta was cooked al dente which I really appreciated. It's a bit pricey, but you're getting restaurant-quality food and enough to feed two people honestly. The value is definitely there and the taste is phenomenal. This is my new comfort food!

The loaded nachos were alright, nothing amazing but not terrible either. The portion was pretty generous, probably good for sharing between two people. The chips were crunchy which was nice, but the toppings were kind of hit or miss. There was plenty of cheese and sour cream, but the meat was a bit bland and I could barely taste any seasoning. The jalapenos added some kick though. For the price, it's reasonably priced and fills you up, so I'd say it's decent value. The flavors just didn't wow me like I hoped they would. Might order again if I'm craving nachos but it wouldn't be my first choice.

Seriously the worst chicken tenders I've ever had. The portion was laughable - only 3 tiny strips! The breading was soggy and flavorless, like they didn't season it at all or maybe just reheated old tenders. The chicken inside was dry and stringy, not tender at all which is ironic given the name. The price is completely ridiculous for what you get. My 6-year-old nephew gets bigger portions at the school cafeteria. I feel like I got scammed honestly. Save your money and order literally anything else.

The cheesecake here is absolutely divine! It's so creamy and smooth with this rich, tangy flavor that's perfectly balanced with the sweetness. The graham cracker crust is buttery and has a nice crunch to it. The slice they give you is a really good size - not too small but not so huge that you feel sick after. It was super affordable. I've had cheesecake at fancy restaurants that cost twice as much and weren't nearly as good. The texture is just perfect, melts in your mouth. If you have a sweet tooth, you absolutely have to try this!

The Buffalo chicken wrap was kind of middle-of-the-road for me. The portion size is okay, fills you up for lunch but nothing spectacular. The Buffalo sauce had a decent kick to it but the flavor was pretty one-dimensional - just spicy without much depth. The chicken was a bit rubbery and there wasn't quite enough of it compared to all the lettuce they packed in there. For the price, I think it's slightly overpriced for what you're getting. It's edible and convenient if you're in a rush, but the flavors just don't come together that well. I probably won't get it again when there are better wrap options on the menu.
